LONDON: Ticket packages for the Jeddah leg of the LIV Golf Invitational Series have been announced on Saturday, according to LIV Golf and QuintEvents. The pair announced their official partnership for all ticketing and hospitality offerings starting with the inaugural eight-event series. Royal Greens Golf Club in Jeddah will host the penultimate event of the series in October. Ticket packages range from grounds passes to premium VIP access, providing amenities for fans including course and player access, luxury dining, inside the ropes access, executive Q&A’s, and player meet & greets. LIV Golf fans also have the opportunity to take advantage of the newest currency trend, as LIV Golf events will also be accepting Cryptocurrency as payment for each of the ticket packages. “QuintEvents is excited to be the official ticket provider for LIV Golf and to help bring this new and exciting version of golf to fans around the world,” said Brian Ruede, President and COO of QuintEvents. “Going above and beyond on fan experience is what we strive to do at QuintEvents, and this will be no exception. LIV Golf Invitational Series ticket packages will include premier access and unique opportunities to experience the sport in ways that golf fans dream of.” The LIV Golf Invitational 2022 schedule is as follows: June 9 – 11: Centurion Golf Club – London July 1 – 3: Pumpkin Ridge Golf Club – Portland July 29 – 31: Trump National Golf Club Bedminster – New Jersey Sept 2 – 4: The International – Boston Sept 16 – 18: Rich Harvest Farms – Chicago Oct 7 – 9: Stonehill – Bangkok Oct 14 – 16: Royal Greens Golf Club – Jeddah Oct 28 – 30: Team Championship